highlights.description: Woman stating that she's not fond of tiny towns because everybody knows what everybody's doing. This might be interesting to play in a tiny WI town.
Colleen remarking that she has found syringes on her lawn, is concerned about drugs.
Worries about gentrification of the south side
Police officer, participating as a citizen, talking about how he wishes people would not automatically extend the national narrative of police brutality to the Madison community
Access to parks and well manicured open spaces is a benefit of Madison.  (perhaps neighborhood specific)
There is a concern for drug usage in her neighborhood.
Concern for the effects of gentrification driving out long-term residents because of higher property taxes.
There is a concern for broader issues related to racism and police brutality.
Madison is progressive, but disparities are still prevalent across several areas. Meaningful shifts need to occur.
